# Design Updates v4 - Typography, Navigation & Critical Review

## 1. Typography & Readability Review

### Current Issues to Address

**Desktop (1024px+)**
- Hero title "Koos Simons" - Ensure 48-64px, sufficient contrast
- Subtitle "Product Manager — Lisbon" - 20-24px, reduce if too large
- Card headings - 24-28px recommended
- Card body text - 16-18px for comfortable reading
- About section body - 18-20px for main content
- Line height: 1.5-1.7 for body text, 1.2-1.3 for headings

**Mobile (320px-768px)**
- Hero title - Scale down to 36-42px
- Subtitle - 18-20px
- Card headings - 20-22px
- Body text - 16px minimum (never smaller)
- Increase line height to 1.6-1.8 for easier reading
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px for all interactive elements

**Typography Hierarchy Issues**
- Ensure clear visual hierarchy: H1 > H2 > H3 > Body
- Card titles should be visually distinct from body text
- Section headings need more weight/size differentiation
- Consistent font weights (300 light, 400 regular, 600 semibold, 700 bold)

### Recommendations

**Font Stack**
```css
/* Headings */
font-family: 'Inter', 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;

/* Body */
font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
```

**Responsive Scale**
- Use `clamp()` for fluid typography: `clamp(36px, 5vw, 64px)` for H1
- Ensures smooth scaling across all screen sizes
- Better than breakpoint-based font sizes

**Readability**
- Maximum line length: 65-75 characters (about 600-700px width)
- Constrain text containers, especially on large screens
- Add max-width to content sections
- Increase paragraph spacing (margin-bottom: 1.5em)

---

## 2. Card Navigation Plan - Linking Cards to Experience

### Proposed Architecture

**Concept:** Click profile card → Scroll/navigate to relevant work experience examples

**Option A: Anchor Links (Recommended for v1)**
- Each of 3 profile cards links to a section below
- Smooth scroll to "Experience Examples" section
- Organize experiences into 3 categories matching cards:
  1. Discovery to Release → Projects focused on 0→1 product development
  2. Data & AI Products → Analytics/AI feature examples
  3. Delivery & Leadership → Stakeholder management examples

**Option B: Modal/Overlay**
- Click card → Opens modal with detailed case studies
- Better for richer content (images, metrics, timelines)
- More complex to implement
- Recommended for v2

**Option C: Separate Pages**
- Each card links to `/discovery`, `/data-ai`, `/delivery`
- Dedicated page per capability area
- Best for extensive portfolios
- Overkill for initial version

### Recommended Approach: Option A (Anchor Links)

**Structure:**
```
[Hero Section]
[About Section]
[3 Profile Cards] ← Clickable
[Availability Section]
[Experience Examples] ← New section
  ├─ Discovery Projects
  ├─ Data & AI Projects
  └─ Delivery Projects
[Contact/Footer]
```

**Implementation Plan:**

1. **Add IDs to target sections**
   - `id="discovery-examples"`
   - `id="data-ai-examples"`
   - `id="delivery-examples"`

2. **Make cards clickable**
   ```jsx
   <Link href="#discovery-examples" className="card">
     [Card content]
   </Link>
   ```

3. **Add smooth scroll behavior**
   ```css
   html {
     scroll-behavior: smooth;
   }
   ```

4. **Visual feedback**
   - Hover: subtle lift/shadow increase
   - Cursor: pointer
   - Optional: small arrow/icon indicating clickability

5. **Create "Experience Examples" section**
   - 3 subsections (one per capability)
   - 2-3 concrete examples per subsection
   - Format: Company/Project name, Role, Brief outcome (1-2 sentences max)
   - Keep concise - details go in resume/case studies

**Example Experience Format:**
```
Discovery to Release Examples:
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
GenAI Knowledge Synthesis Tool - Nike
Turned ambiguous "AI for product teams" request into scoped MVP. 
Shipped v1 in 3 months, 70% team adoption in first quarter.

Data Governance Platform - Rabobank  
Defined 0→1 roadmap through 15+ stakeholder interviews.
Separated immediate quick wins from 18-month platform vision.
```

**Mobile Considerations:**
- Ensure scroll offset accounts for fixed headers
- Add "Back to top" button after scrolling to examples
- Consider sticky section nav when viewing examples

---

## 3. Critical Design Review

### ✅ Strengths

**Professional Appearance**
- Clean, modern dark theme
- Good use of whitespace (once spacing issues fixed)
- Professional color palette (navy/teal accents work well)
- Consistent card-based layout

**Information Hierarchy**
- Clear hero → about → capabilities flow
- Profile cards effectively communicate core strengths
- Availability section addresses recruiter needs directly

**Technical Implementation**
- Modern stack (Next.js/Tailwind)
- Should be performant and maintainable
- Easy content updates via YAML

### ⚠️ Areas for Improvement

**Originality: 6/10**
- Layout is conventional (hero → cards → content)
- Dark theme is trendy but common in tech portfolios
- Card grid is standard pattern
- **Fix:** Add subtle unique elements:
  - Custom illustrations/icons (you have SVGs - use them prominently)
  - Unique section transitions
  - Personal branding element (custom accent color, unique layout for one section)

**Visual Interest: 7/10**
- Current design is clean but potentially flat
- Lacks visual hierarchy depth
- **Fix:** 
  - Add subtle gradients or texture to hero
  - Use varied card heights/layouts
  - Include project screenshots or data visualizations
  - More prominent use of your custom SVG icons

**Differentiation: 6/10**
- Looks similar to many PM portfolios
- Nothing memorable or "sticky"
- **Fix:**
  - Add one signature element (unique animation, custom illustration, interactive element)
  - Consider brief animated data visualization showing impact
  - Personal photo should be professional but show personality

**Mobile Experience: 8/10** (pending typography fixes)
- Layout adapts well
- Cards stack appropriately
- **Concerns:**
  - Need to verify touch targets (44x44px min)
  - Text sizing needs review
  - Hero might still be too tall on mobile even at 50%

**Professional Credibility: 8/10**
- Clean, serious design appropriate for PM role
- Good balance of skills showcase + availability
- **Missing:**
  - No metrics/outcomes visible (add to experience examples)
  - No client logos or company references (consider adding)
  - No social proof (testimonials, recommendations)

### ❌ Critical Issues

**Typography Hierarchy**
- Current: Insufficient differentiation between heading levels
- Impact: Reduces scanability and professionalism
- **Fix:** Implement typography scale in v4

**Readability on Large Screens**
- Current: Text likely stretches too wide on 1440px+ monitors
- Impact: Harder to read, looks unfinished
- **Fix:** Add max-width containers (600-800px for text, 1200px for layout)

**Interactive Feedback**
- Current: Cards may not signal they're clickable
- Impact: Users miss navigation opportunities
- **Fix:** Add hover states, cursor changes, subtle animations

**Content Density**
- Current: Some sections might feel sparse
- Impact: Looks incomplete or lightweight
- **Fix:** Add experience examples section, more concrete outcomes

